#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.43:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga"
msgstr "5. About Dhammika"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Nāgasutta"
msgstr "43. The Giant"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.345"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an6.43:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiyaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "an6.43:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he addressed Venerable "
"Ānanda:"

msgctxt "an6.43:1.4"
msgid ""
"“āyāmānanda, yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkamissāma "
"divāvihārāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of "
"Migāra’s mother for the day’s meditation.”"

msgctxt "an6.43:1.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo "
"tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the Eastern Monastery."

msgctxt "an6.43:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"In the late afternoon the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed Ānanda:"

msgctxt "an6.43:2.3"
msgid ""
"“āyāmānanda, yena pubbakoṭṭhako tenupasaṅkamissāma gattāni parisiñcitun”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the eastern gate to bathe.”"

msgctxt "an6.43:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "an6.43:2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena pubbakoṭṭhako tenupasaṅkami "
"gattāni parisiñcituṃ."
msgstr "So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the eastern gate to bathe."

msgctxt "an6.43:2.6"
msgid ""
"Pubbakoṭṭhake gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni "
"pubbāpayamāno."
msgstr ""
"When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying "
"himself."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.346"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: mahātūriyatāḷitavāditena → mahāturiyatālita … (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa seto nāma nāgo "
"mahātūriyatāḷitavāditena pubbakoṭṭhakā paccuttarati."
msgstr ""
"Now, at that time King Pasenadi had a giant bull elephant called “White”. It "
"emerged from the eastern gate to the beating and playing of musical "
"instruments."

msgctxt "an6.43:3.2"
msgid "Apissu taṃ jano disvā evamāha:"
msgstr "When people saw it they exclaimed:"

# BB includes the extra phrase “nago vata bho nago” here, however, it is absent from most editions so I don’t include it.
msgctxt "an6.43:3.3"
msgid ""
"“abhirūpo vata bho rañño nāgo; dassanīyo vata bho rañño nāgo; pāsādiko vata, "
"bho, rañño nāgo, kāyupapanno vata bho rañño nāgo”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The royal giant is so handsome! The royal giant is so good-looking! The "
"royal giant is so lovely! The royal giant has such a huge body!”"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When they said this, Venerable Udāyī said to the Buddha:"

#. VAR: mahantaṃ brahantaṃ → mahantaṃ bruhantaṃ (bj) | mahattaṃ brahmattaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.5"
msgid ""
"“hatthimeva nu kho, bhante, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā "
"evamāha:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, is it only when they see elephants with such a huge, formidable body "
"that people exclaim:"

#. VAR: kañci → kiñci (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘nāgo vata bho nāgo’ti, udāhu aññampi kañci mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ "
"jano disvā evamāha: ‘nāgo vata bho nāgo’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘A giant, such a giant’? Or do they say it when they see any other creatures "
"with huge, formidable bodies?”"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.7"
msgid ""
"“Hatthimpi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā evamāha:"
msgstr ""
"“Udāyī, when they see elephants with such a huge, formidable body people "
"exclaim:"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.8"
msgid "‘nāgo vata bho nāgo’ti."
msgstr "‘A giant, such a giant!’"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.9"
msgid "Assampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "And also when they see a horse with a huge, formidable body …"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.10"
msgid "goṇampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "When they see a bull with a huge, formidable body …"

#. VAR: uragampi → nāgampi (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.11"
msgid "uragampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "When they see a snake with a huge, formidable body …"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.12"
msgid "rukkhampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "When they see a tree with a huge, formidable body …"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.13"
msgid ""
"manussampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā evamāha:"
msgstr ""
"And when they see a human being with such a huge, formidable body people "
"exclaim:"

msgctxt "an6.43:3.14"
msgid "‘nāgo vata, bho, nāgo’ti."
msgstr "‘A giant, such a giant!’"

# By using monstrous I am trying to echo the pun in the text. Not very good, perhaps, but neither is the original!
msgctxt "an6.43:3.15"
msgid ""
"Api ca, udāyi, yo sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā "
"pajāya sadevamanussāya āguṃ na karoti kāyena vācāya manasā, tamahaṃ ‘nāgo’ti "
"brūmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But Udāyī, one who does nothing monstrous by way of body, speech, and mind "
"is who I call a ‘giant’ in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, "
"this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:4.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an6.43:4.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā—"
msgstr "How well said this was by the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an6.43:4.3"
msgid ""
"api ca, udāyi, yo sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā "
"pajāya sadevamanussāya āguṃ na karoti kāyena vācāya manasā, tamahaṃ ‘nāgo’ti "
"brūmīti."
msgstr ""
"‘But Udāyī, one who does nothing monstrous by way of body, speech, and mind "
"is who I call a “giant” in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, "
"this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.’"

msgctxt "an6.43:4.4"
msgid "Idañca panāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā subhāsitaṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumodāmi—"
msgstr "And I celebrate the well-spoken words of the Buddha with these verses:"

# My translation here follows, with a few adjustments, my earlier translation of Thag 15.2.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.1"
msgid "Manussabhūtaṃ sambuddhaṃ,"
msgstr "Awakened as a human being,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.2"
msgid "attadantaṃ samāhitaṃ;"
msgstr "self-tamed and immersed in samādhi,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.3"
msgid "Iriyamānaṃ brahmapathe,"
msgstr "following the spiritual path,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.4"
msgid "cittassūpasame rataṃ."
msgstr "he loves peace of mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:6.1"
msgid "Yaṃ manussā namassanti,"
msgstr "Revered by people,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:6.2"
msgid "sabbadhammāna pāraguṃ;"
msgstr "gone beyond all things,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: taṃ → naṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:6.3"
msgid "Devāpi taṃ namassanti,"
msgstr "even the gods revere him;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:6.4"
msgid "iti me arahato sutaṃ."
msgstr "so I’ve heard from the perfected one."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:7.1"
msgid "Sabbasaṃyojanātītaṃ,"
msgstr "He has transcended all fetters"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nibbanamāgataṃ → nibbāna … (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:7.2"
msgid "vanā nibbanamāgataṃ;"
msgstr "and escaped from entanglements."

#. <br>
#. VAR: nekkhammarataṃ → nekkhamme rataṃ (si)
msgctxt "an6.43:7.3"
msgid "Kāmehi nekkhammarataṃ,"
msgstr "Delighting to renounce sensual pleasures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:7.4"
msgid "muttaṃ selāva kañcanaṃ."
msgstr "he’s freed like gold from stone."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.1"
msgid "Sabbe accarucī nāgo,"
msgstr "That giant outshines all,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.2"
msgid "himavāññe siluccaye;"
msgstr "like the Himalaya beside other mountains."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.3"
msgid "Sabbesaṃ nāganāmānaṃ,"
msgstr "Of all those named ‘giant’,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.4"
msgid "saccanāmo anuttaro."
msgstr "he is truly named, supreme."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: vo → te (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:9.1"
msgid "Nāgaṃ vo kittayissāmi,"
msgstr "I’ll extol the giant for you,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:9.2"
msgid "na hi āguṃ karoti so;"
msgstr "for he does nothing monstrous."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:9.3"
msgid "Soraccaṃ avihiṃsā ca,"
msgstr "Gentleness and harmlessness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:9.4"
msgid "pādā nāgassa te duve."
msgstr "are two feet of the giant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.1"
msgid "Tapo ca brahmacariyaṃ,"
msgstr "Austerity and celibacy"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.2"
msgid "caraṇā nāgassa tyāpare;"
msgstr "are his two other feet."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.3"
msgid "Saddhāhattho mahānāgo,"
msgstr "Faith is the giant’s trunk,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.4"
msgid "upekkhāsetadantavā."
msgstr "and equanimity his white tusks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.1"
msgid "Sati gīvā siro paññā,"
msgstr "Mindfulness is his neck, his head is wisdom—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.2"
msgid "vīmaṃsā dhammacintanā;"
msgstr "investigation and thinking about principles."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.3"
msgid "Dhammakucchisamātapo,"
msgstr "His belly is the sacred hearth of the Dhamma,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.4"
msgid "viveko tassa vāladhi."
msgstr "and his tail is seclusion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:12.1"
msgid "So jhāyī assāsarato,"
msgstr "Practicing absorption, enjoying the breath,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ajjhattaṃ susamāhito → ajjhattūpasamāhito (s1-3) | ajjhattupasamāhito (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:12.2"
msgid "ajjhattaṃ susamāhito;"
msgstr "he is serene within."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:12.3"
msgid "Gacchaṃ samāhito nāgo,"
msgstr "The giant is serene when walking,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:12.4"
msgid "ṭhito nāgo samāhito."
msgstr "the giant is serene when standing,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.347"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.1"
msgid "Seyyaṃ samāhito nāgo,"
msgstr "the giant is serene when lying down,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.2"
msgid "nisinnopi samāhito;"
msgstr "and when sitting, the giant is serene."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.3"
msgid "Sabbattha saṃvuto nāgo,"
msgstr "The giant is restrained everywhere:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.4"
msgid "esā nāgassa sampadā."
msgstr "this is the accomplishment of the giant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.1"
msgid "Bhuñjati anavajjāni,"
msgstr "He eats blameless things,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.2"
msgid "sāvajjāni na bhuñjati;"
msgstr "he doesn’t eat blameworthy things."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.3"
msgid "Ghāsamacchādanaṃ laddhā,"
msgstr "When he gets food and clothes,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.4"
msgid "sannidhiṃ parivajjayaṃ."
msgstr "he avoids storing them up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.1"
msgid "Saṃyojanaṃ aṇuṃ thūlaṃ,"
msgstr "Having severed all bonds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.2"
msgid "sabbaṃ chetvāna bandhanaṃ;"
msgstr "fetters large and small,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.3"
msgid "Yena yeneva gacchati,"
msgstr "wherever he goes,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.4"
msgid "anapekkhova gacchati."
msgstr "he goes without concern."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:16.1"
msgid "Yathāpi udake jātaṃ,"
msgstr "A white lotus,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:16.2"
msgid "puṇḍarīkaṃ pavaḍḍhati;"
msgstr "fragrant and delightful,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Nupalippati → na upalippati (bj, s1, km, pts1) | na upalimpati (s2, s3) | nupalimpati (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:16.3"
msgid "Nupalippati toyena,"
msgstr "sprouts in water and grows there,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:16.4"
msgid "sucigandhaṃ manoramaṃ."
msgstr "but the water doesn’t cling to it."

# BB has “well-born”, but I suspect lokesu is merely a locative plural metri causa. The parallel line in Tag 15.2 lacks su, inserting a ca instead.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.1"
msgid "Tatheva loke sujāto,"
msgstr "Just so the Buddha is born in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.2"
msgid "buddho loke viharati;"
msgstr "and lives in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.3"
msgid "Nupalippati lokena,"
msgstr "but the world doesn’t stick to him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.4"
msgid "toyena padumaṃ yathā."
msgstr "as the water does not stick to the lotus."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
#. VAR: Mahāginīva jalito → mahāggini pajjalito (bj, s1-3, km) | mahāgini pajjalito (pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:18.1"
msgid "Mahāginīva jalito,"
msgstr "A great blazing fire"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:18.2"
msgid "anāhārūpasammati;"
msgstr "dies down when the fuel runs out."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Saṅkhāresūpasantesu → aṅgāresu ca santesu (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:18.3"
msgid "Saṅkhāresūpasantesu,"
msgstr "When the coals have gone out"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:18.4"
msgid "nibbutoti pavuccati."
msgstr "it’s said to be ‘extinguished’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:19.1"
msgid "Atthassāyaṃ viññāpanī,"
msgstr "This simile is taught by the discerning"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:19.2"
msgid "upamā viññūhi desitā;"
msgstr "to express the meaning clearly."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Viññassanti → viññāyanti (s1-3) | viññissanti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:19.3"
msgid "Viññassanti mahānāgā,"
msgstr "Great giants will understand"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:19.4"
msgid "nāgaṃ nāgena desitaṃ."
msgstr "what the giant taught the giant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an6.43:20.1"
msgid "Vītarāgo vītadoso,"
msgstr "Free of greed, free of hate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:20.2"
msgid "Vītamoho anāsavo;"
msgstr "free of delusion, undefiled;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:20.3"
msgid "Sarīraṃ vijahaṃ nāgo,"
msgstr "the giant, giving up his body,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Parinibbissati → parinibbāti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:20.4"
msgid "Parinibbissati anāsavo”ti."
msgstr "will become extinguished without defilements.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.43:20.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
